result.name: badchar
result.description: A parse error indicates a malformed XML document; for example, a document that contains an illegal character, mismatched element end-tags or trailing content after the document element. Examine the specific error message and correct the XML document.

result.name: outofmemory
result.description: An out of memory error indicates memory depletion while parsing of an XML document. Memory depletion can result from an excessively large document, a main document that includes large amounts of external data, or explosive entity expansion.

result.name: metrics
result.description: The XML parser has user configurable limits on various characteristics of an XML document, to include document size, element nesting depth and the number of attributes on a single element. This error indicates that a document exceeded one of those limits and was rejected. If document rejection is the behavior you want, no action is required; if the document should not be rejected, correct the problem by reconfiguring the limits to accept the rejected document.

result.name: forbiddendtd
result.description: An XML Firewall service has rejected a SOAP message because the message contained a DTD (Document Type Declaration). Such messages are not allowed by the SOAP standard. Correct the problem by removing the DTD from the XML document or by reconfiguring the XML Firewall service to a non-soap parsing mode, such as "xml" or "unprocessed".

result.name: forbiddenpi
result.text: Processing instruction encountered in SOAP context
result.description: An XML Firewall service has rejected a SOAP message because the message contained a PI (Processing Instruction). Such messages are not allowed by the SOAP standard. Correct the problem by removing the processing instruction from the XML document or by reconfiguring the XML Firewall service to a non-SOAP parsing mode, such as "xml" or "unprocessed".

result.name: aborted
result.description: This error indicates that an external service has interrupted the parser and ordered it to stop, though no XML parse error may have occurred. This can happen, for example, if a network service such an XML Firewall has to close a connection and there is no need to finish a parse in a process. Examine the other log messages surrounding this one to determine the root cause of the problem.

result.name: internal
result.description: An internal error occurred in the parser; contact DataPower for support.

result.name: maxchunksize
result.description: The XML parser has a user configurable limit on the maximum size of any single node in an XML document. This error indicates that a node in a document has exceeded this limit and has been rejected. If document rejection is the behavior you want, no action is required; if the document should not have been rejected, correct the problem by increasing the maximum node size allowed on the XML manager associated with this service.

result.name: forbiddenexternal
result.text: Forbidden external reference encountered while parsing XML
result.description: In some contexts, the XML parser has a user configurable toggle that determines if the xml parser will retrieve external documents to resolve external DTD or external entity references in the input document. This error indicates that an external reference has been encountered in an input document when the parser has been configured to reject such references. If document rejection is the behavior you want, no action is required; if the document should not have been rejected, correct the problem by enabling external references on the XML manager associated with this service. Note that some contexts such as GatewayScript do not allow the more lenient setting.

result.name: outofmemory2
result.text: Out of memory due to max-node-size too small
result.description: The XML parser has run out of memory while parsing an XML document due to the value of the max-node-size parser limit. Try returning the max-node-size parser limit on the appropriate XML Manager or Service object to the default 32MB.

result.name: streamerror
result.description: A read error indicates an I/O error in the data stream the XML document handler is reading from, for example a reset connection, a network protocol error, and so forth. Examine other log messages surrounding this one to determine the root cause of the problem.

result.name: connecterror
result.description: A connect error indicates an error that prevented the establishment of a connection between the DataPower Gateway and the source of an XML document, for example an invalid URL, a refused connection, and so forth. Examine other log messages surrounding this one to determine the root cause of the problem.

result.name: dynamic
result.description: A dynamic execution error indicates some sort of illegal XSLT operation occurred. An example would be calling a template that does not exist, or misusing a variable's value (such as an illegal use of a number as a nodeset). Examine the error logs and repair the stylesheet.

result.name: static
result.description: A static compilation error indicates that a stylesheet cannot be prepared for execution because it is invalid according to the XSLT specification. For example, if a stylesheet contained typos in the name of an XSLT command and as a result had an illegal element name, it would be a static error because the stylesheet cannot be executed. Examine the stylesheet error log and repair the stylesheet.

result.name: outputerror
result.description: An error has occurred on output, which indicates that the network connection failed or some other output error. The processing of the stylesheet was stopped. Examine the error logs to find more details.

result.name: pcre
result.description: An error occurred when processing a regular expression match. The execution of the stylesheet has been terminated. Examine the error logs to find more details.

result.name: pending

result.name: nomemory

result.name: http2_proxynotsupported
result.text: Cannot configure HTTP/2 support using TLS proxy profile.
result.description: If HTTP/2 support is enabled, it cannot use the TLS proxy profile.
result.suggestion: Change the TLS configuration to use an TLS server profile or an TLS SNI server profile.

result.name: http2_tls12_required
result.text: Cannot configure HTTP/2 support without TLS 1.2 protocol.
result.description: If HTTP/2 support is enabled, the TLS server profile or the TLS SNI server profile must have the TLS 1.2 protocol enabled.
result.suggestion: Change the TLS configuration of the TLS server profile or the TLS SNI server profile and enable the TLS 1.2 protocol.

result.name: http2_no_cipher
result.text: Cannot configure HTTP/2 support without a supported cipher.
result.description: If HTTP/2 support is enabled, the TLS server profile or the TLS SNI server profile must support a cipher for HTTP/2 in the cipher list.
result.suggestion: Change the configuration of the TLS server profile or the TLS SNI server profile and add at least one of the following ciphers: DHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256, DHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384, DHE_DSS_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256, DHE_DSS_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384, ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256, ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384, ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256 or ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384.

result.name: http2_unsupported_upgrade
result.text: Cannot upgrade http to HTTP/2 with another protocol.
result.description: If HTTP/2 support is enabled, the upgrade request cannot contain another protocol.
result.suggestion: Make sure the upgrade header only contains the HTTP/2 clear text protocol: h2c.

result.name: http2_compression_disallowed
result.text: Cannot configure HTTP/2 support with an TLS server profile which has compression enabled.
result.description: If HTTP/2 support is enabled, the TLS server profile must not have compression enabled.
result.suggestion: Change the TLS configuration of the TLS server profile and disable compression.

result.name: http2_renegotiation_disallowed
result.text: Cannot configure HTTP/2 support with an TLS server profile which has renegotiation enabled.
result.description: If HTTP/2 support is enabled, the TLS server profile must not have renegotiation enabled.
result.suggestion: Change the TLS configuration of the TLS server profile and disable renegotiation (either set the maximum number of negotiations to 0 or prohibt session resume on renegotiation).

result.name: EBMS_LOWLEVEL_FAULT_RESPONSE
result.text: Fault response returned by outbound receiver
result.summary: Received fault response returned by outbound receiver
result.description: The receiver responded a fault response where the error was generally not at the level of ebMS transport. Most likely a HTTP 500 Error and SOAP-related errors. ebMS v2.0 leverages SOAP Fault semantics for low level SOAP-related errors, and specifies higher level "ebMS error lists" that can be comprised of a list of warnings and or errors that occur at the ebMS transport level. For example, a SOAP syntax error will generally result in a SOAP Fault error reply.

result.description: The SSH Client Connection of the sftp destination references an SSH Client Profile with an incorrect usage. The Profile Usage of the SSH Client Connection must be sftp.
result.suggestion: Verify that every destination whose Destination URL starts with sftp:// utilizes an SSH Client Profile with a Profile Usage of sftp.

result.name: CONFIG_MISSING_BUSINESS_ID

result.suggestion: Check the partner profiles of the internal partner and external partner that are associated in the CPA entry. The type (internal or external) of the partner profiles must exactly match what you bind, and the partner profiles bound to the CPA entry must be attached to the partner profiles in the B2B Gateway Service.

result.suggestion: Check the CPA entries at the B2B Gateway Service configuration page.

result.name: EBMSCPA_CANNOT_FIND_MSHSERVICE

result.summary: Cannot identify a CPA Collaboration for delivering ebMS MSH level signals.

result.suggestion: Check the CPA entries at the B2B Gateway Service configuration page.

result.name: EBMSCPA_CANNOT_RECOGONIZE_RECEIVING_ACTION
result.summary: Cannot identify the receiving Action binding.
result.description: The DataPower Gateway received a well-formed and valid ebMS message, but cannot identify any ebMS CPA receiving Action binding in the B2B Gateway Service.
result.suggestion: Ensure that the values in the ebMS message are correctly configured.

result.name: EBMSCPA_INCONSISTENT

result.description: Some values in the inbound ebMS message header does not match the values in the CPA settings.
result.suggestion: Ensure that the values in the ebMS message are correctly configured.

result.name: EBMS_NO_REPLYACTION
result.text: Cannot reply with no MSH Signal Service
result.summary: Cannot reply without MSH Signal Service defined.
result.description: An MSH Signal Service is required in the following cases in an inbound gateway: * when receiving an ebMS message that requests for an Asynchronous Acknowledgment; * when receiving an ebMS message that requests for a signed Acknowledgment * when an Asynchronous Error is being reported * when an Asynchronous Pong and a StatusResponse is being sent. An error occurs if no MSH Signal Service is defined for the matched <CPAId, Internal Party, External Party>.

result.name: CONFIG_MISSINGPROP_SERVICE
result.summary: A missing required property 'Service'.
result.description: A required property 'Service' is missing.
result.suggestion: Specify the 'Service' property in the CPA configuration.

result.name: CONFIG_MISSINGPROP_ROLE
result.summary: Missing required properties 'Internal Role' or 'External Role'.
result.description: A service is either a business collaboration service or an MSH signal service. If using a business collaboration service, you must specify the internal and external roles in the CPA configuration.
result.suggestion: Specify the authorized role of the internal or external partner in a business collaboration service.

result.name: CONFIG_MISSINGPROP_DEFAULTSIGNAL
result.summary: Missing Default MSH Signal Sender and Receiver.
result.description: A service is either a business collaboration service or an MSH signal service. If using an MSH signal service, you must specify the default MSH signal sender and receiver in the CPA configuration.
result.suggestion: Specify the Default MSH Signal Sender and Receiver in a MSH signal service.

result.name: CONFIG_MISSINGPROP_ACTIONS
result.summary: No Action configured.
result.description: A service is either a business collaboration service or an MSH signal service. If using a business collaboration service, at least one Action is required in the CPA configuration.
result.suggestion: Specify at least one CPA Action in a business collaboration service.

result.name: EBMSCPA_CANNOT_RECOGONIZE_SENDING_ACTION
result.summary: Cannot identify sending Action binding.
result.description: The DataPower Gateway received a well-formed and valid ebMS message, but cannot identify any ebMS CPA sending Action binding in the B2B Gateway Service.
result.suggestion: Ensure that the values in the ebMS message are correctly configured.

result.name: EBMS_CANNOT_SIGN_ACK
result.summary: Failed to generate signature of Acknowledgment.
result.description: An inbound message requests a signed Acknowledgment, but the required configurations are not properly set. The required configurations include the working Identification Credentials, algorithms to sign the Acknowledgment and create the digest value, and the canonicalization method.
result.suggestion: For a CPA-enforced B2B gateway, check the Acknowledgment Sender setting; for non-CPA-enforced B2B gateway, check the ebMS settings of the internal partner profile.

result.name: EBMS_PACKAGING_PROCESS_FAILED
result.text: Processing failure: Failed to package outbound ebMS message
result.summary: Processing failure: Failed to package outbound ebMS message.
result.description: A processing error occurred when DataPower Gateway packages the outbound ebMS message before delivering the message to the external partner. The packaging processor might stop because of failures in security operation such as encryption and signing process.
result.suggestion: Ensure that the configurations are defined appropriately.

result.name: EBMS_MISSING_IDENT_INFO
result.text: Missing required CPAId, Service, or Action
result.summary: Missing required identification information for packaging ebMS MessageHeader.
result.description: CPAId, Service, and Action are the required identification information for ebMS routing. In outbound transactions, CPAId, Service, and Action are packaged in the ebMS MessageHeader. The message cannot be packaged if any of the values is missing.
result.suggestion: Specify the values in the custom processing policy, the Destination, or the Partner Profile ebMS Settings. Ensure that the values of CPAId, Service, and Action are all extracted.

result.name: DB_QUERY_RESULT_INVALID
result.text: Query result from database is invalid
result.summary: Returned query result from database is invalid
result.description: DB query is success but returned query result from database is either invalid or empty.

result.name: EBMS_PACKAGING_REPLYPROCESS_FAILED
result.text: Processing failure: Failed to package Acknowledgment
result.summary: Processing failure: Failed to package ebMS Acknowledgment or Error for replying inbound ebMS request.
result.description: A processing error occurred during packaging ebMS Acknowledgment or Error signal before the attempt to deliver the response signal to the external partner. The packaging processor might stop because of failures in security operation such as encryption and signing process.
result.suggestion: Check the logging message and ensure that the configurations are defined appropriately.

result.name: EDI_PARSE_ERROR
result.text: An error ocurred when parsing EDI document
result.summary: An error ocurred when parsing EDI document.
result.description: An error ocurred when parsing EDI document.
result.suggestion: Check the document and ensure it conforms with EDI specification.

result.description: Error happened during archiving transaction.
result.suggestion: Check archive target is available.

result.name: ARCHIVE_DIR_NOTVALID
result.summary: The Archive Directory URL uses an invalid directory or a protocol scheme not supported in archive destination.
result.description: Each B2B Gateway can have an archive location to upload the transaction data (containing transaction metadata and document payloads) off the DataPower Gateway or locally. The supported off-DataPower Gateway archiving types are: NFS (dpnfs://), FTP and FTPS (ftp://), SFTP (sftp://), HTTP (http://), and HTTPS (https://). To store locally in RAID volume, specifies a subdirectory in the attached Hard Disk Array object; for example, local:///ondisk.
result.suggestion: Change the Archive Directory URL field to use a supported protocol scheme.

result.name: DOC_STORE_NOTACCESSIBLE
result.summary: The document storage location is not accessible
result.description: The configured directory of storage location for B2B documents was not accessible when the B2B Gateway object is committed. This is possibly occurring when using a remote directory under NFS mount (nfs-name:) or iSCSI directory (local:///my-iscsi-dir).
result.suggestion: Check the existence of the configured directory and re-enable the B2B Gateway object; for example, using CLI "dir" command to see the directory show up in the output list and clicking "Apply" to attempt to bring up the B2B Gateway object.

result.name: HA_NOCONFIG_TEMPLATE

result.description: Failed to generate HA configuration file.

result.summary: The IPv6 address is not supported for high availability configuration..
result.description: The IPv6 address is not supported for high availability configuration..

result.name: HA_INVALID_CONFIGURATION

result.description: The received message is signed with unsupported digest algorithm, or it use an algorithm that is banned under certain crypto mode.

result.name: DOC_STORE_NOTREADY
result.text: B2B document storage is not ready to be used.
result.summary: The B2B document storage is not properly configured.
result.description: The B2B gateway services require the RAID volume with the support of metadata storage and document storage. This error is most likely the file system of the RAID volume is not initialized with B2B storage so that the document storage partition is not availble.
result.suggestion: Make sure the RAID volume is created with B2B storage where you can visit the RAID Partition status provider to check that two partitions are available for metadata and document storage.

result.name: ROUTINGPREPROCESSOR_TYPE_MISMATCH
result.summary: The B2B document routing preprocessor file does not match the selected processor type.
result.description: The file type, inferred by the extension of the specified routing preprocessor file, must match the selected processor type. A GatewayScript processor type must be used with a JS file. A stylesheet processor type can be used with any file formats other than the JS format.
result.suggestion: Review B2B Gateway configurations and ensure that the document routing preprocessor file matches the selected processor type.

result.name: INVALID_CPA_SENDER_TYPE
result.text: One or more CPA senders are not internal partner profiles.
result.summary: A CPA sender in a CPA binding must be an internal partner profile.
result.description: A CPA sender in a CPA binding must be an internal partner profile.
result.suggestion: Review CPA binding configuration and ensure that all CPA senders are internal partner profiles.

result.description: No message is available for pulling in this MPC at this moment. The reason might be that all messages in the MPC are consumed, or the message producer has not submitted the messages to the MPC yet.
result.suggestion: If you still have messages that are not aquired yet, issue another pull request against this MPC later.

result.name: EBMS_POLICY_NONCOMPLIANCE

result.name: EBMS_EXTERNAL_PAYLOAD_ERROR

result.name: EBMS_DECOMPRESSION_FAILURE

result.name: EBMS_UNEXPECT_ENCRYPTED_MESSAGE
result.text: An encrypted message was received while the B2B Gateway expects an unencrypted message.
result.description: See message text.

result.name: EBMS_DATA_NOT_COMPRESSED
result.text: An uncompressed message was received while the B2B Gateway requires a compressed message.
result.description: The partner profile requires inbound data to be compressed, but the message does not appear to be properly compressed.

result.name: EBMS_UNEXPECT_COMPRESSED_MESSAGE
result.text: A compressed message was received while the B2B Gateway expects an uncompressed message.
result.description: See message text.

result.name: EBMS_DEL_MPC_MSG_ABORT
result.text: Failed to delete the specified message from the MPC.
result.description: Error occurs when deleting the specified message from the MPC. This might happen when you attempt to delete multiple messages.

result.name: EBMS_SUBMIT_INVALID_MPCNAME_FAIL
result.text: The MPC name that is associated with the submitted message is invalid.
result.description: The MPC name might include invalid characters.
result.suggestion: Ensure that the MPC name is properly configured in the matched destination settings of the external partner profile.
